<section class="issues">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="text-center">What's Your Audio Issue?</h2>
        <div class="switching">
                        <div class="sec">
                <div class="text"><h3>Don’t Know What Equipment You Need?</h3>
<p>Whether you’re a dorm room producer making hard-hitting beats or a folky singer/songwriter looking to record the next acoustic folk hit, your equipment needs may wary. Browse through the buying guides and gear recommendations to find the right equipment to help you make more music.</p>
                <a class="btn" href="https://www.audio-issues.com/buying-audio-equipment/">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                <div class="image"><img src="https://www.audio-issues.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/home-desktop_10.png" alt=""></div>
            </div>
                        <div class="sec">
                <div class="text"><h3>Want to Set Up a Sweet Sounding Home Studio?</h3>
<p>Creating music in your spare room was a dream for most musicians back in the old days. Not anymore. Setting up a great sounding home studio doesn’t have to be complicated or expensive, but you might not know where to start. Get easy to use practical tips on making your home studio sound as good as possible without spending a fortune.</p>
                <a class="btn" href="https://www.audio-issues.com/setting-up-home-studio/">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                <div class="image"><img src="https://www.audio-issues.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/home-desktop_14.png" alt=""></div>
            </div>
                        <div class="sec">
                <div class="text"><h3>Get it Right at the Source and Learn to Record Instruments and Vocals</h3>
<p>If you’ve finally put your home studio together you might not have a clue about how to record all your instruments. If you’re not sure how to get the best sound at the source you’ll get easy to use guides on planning a successful recording session and easy to use microphone recording techniques that help you get a great sounding performance from your musicians.</p>
                <a class="btn" href="https://www.audio-issues.com/record-instruments-vocals/">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                <div class="image"><img src="https://www.audio-issues.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/home-desktop_16.png" alt=""></div>
            </div>
                        <div class="sec">
                <div class="text"><h3>The Only Music Mixing Tips You’ll Ever Need</h3>
<p>Once you’ve finished recording it’s time to mix those tracks together to make a killer sounding record. Learn everything you need to know about EQ, compression, reverb, delay and saturation to create tight and punchy mixes where you can hear all the instruments in a song.</p>
                <a class="btn" href="https://www.audio-issues.com/mixing-music/">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                <div class="image"><img src="https://www.audio-issues.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/home-desktop_19.png" alt=""></div>
            </div>
                        <div class="sec">
                <div class="text"><h3>Want to Master Your Mixes Together into an Album?</h3>
<p>Mastering is the mysterious voodoo magic of music production that people naively think machines can somehow do for them. Learn the subtle trade of mastering your mixes together as a cohesive record with guides on mastering EQ, multi-band compression, limiting and the importance of metering to stay balanced and dynamic.</p>
                <a class="btn" href="https://www.audio-issues.com/mastering-music-finishing-albumns/">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                <div class="image"><img src="https://www.audio-issues.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/home-desktop_21.png" alt=""></div>
            </div>
                        <div class="sec">
                <div class="text"><h3>Learn How to Become a Kick-Ass Sound Tech All the Bands Love</h3>
<p>Are you struggling to make your live shows sound good? If you’re exhausted with feedback, lousy stage sound and broken cables, then get our live sound guides that help you survive the sound-check and succeed at the show.</p>
                <a class="btn" href="https://www.audio-issues.com/running-live-sound/">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                <div class="image"><img src="https://www.audio-issues.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/home-desktop_25.png" alt=""></div>
            </div>
                        <div class="sec">
                <div class="text"><h3>Earn an Income With Your Professional Music Skills</h3>
<p>If you’re already a highly skilled audio engineer and musician that records your own music, why not use those skills to make some money on the side? Learn how to find what you’re worth, how to price a session, get more gigs and learn to get started in the music industry.</p>
                <a class="btn" href="https://www.audio-issues.com/make-money-in-audio-industry/">Learn More</a>
                </div>
                <div class="image"><img src="https://www.audio-issues.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/home-desktop_28.png" alt=""></div>
            </div>
                    </div>
    </div>
</section>


